WEBVTT

00:07.215 --> 00:08.216
(SIGHS)

00:08.299 --> 00:10.385
I can't believe this trip is almost over.

00:10.552 --> 00:15.181
It's going to feel so good
to hop on a plane and fly back home.

00:15.807 --> 00:19.310
Uh, yeah, okay, of course. We'll fly back.

00:19.394 --> 00:23.690
In the meantime, we can take a load off
and relax at your sister's wedding.

00:23.773 --> 00:26.484
-(BACKFIRING)
-(EXCLAIMING)

00:26.568 --> 00:28.319
(LAUGHS) Mater! What's going on?

00:28.403 --> 00:29.404
-Sorry, buddy.
-(BACKFIRES)

00:29.487 --> 00:32.407
Just thinking about seeing my sister
makes me anxious.

00:32.532 --> 00:34.951
And when I get anxious,
I get the backfires. (GROANS)

00:35.160 --> 00:36.578
Come on, relax.

00:36.745 --> 00:38.830
I'm sure there's nothing to worry about.

00:38.913 --> 00:40.498
You don't understand.

00:40.582 --> 00:43.084
When I get around my sister,

00:43.168 --> 00:46.504
-something unexplainable happens to me.
-(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

00:46.588 --> 00:47.839
(SILENCE)

00:47.922 --> 00:49.674
Ah, she can't be that bad.

00:49.758 --> 00:52.302
She's probably just jealous
'cause you moved somewhere new,

00:52.385 --> 00:55.263
and she never left her humble begin...

00:58.099 --> 01:00.226
-Holy mansion!
-(BACKFIRES)

01:00.894 --> 01:03.438
MAN: (SINGING)
<i>Hittin' the highway, a couple of friends</i>

01:03.521 --> 01:04.939
-(EXCLAIMS)
-(ROARS)

01:05.023 --> 01:06.816
<i>-With new adventures</i>
-(THUNDER BREAKS)

01:06.900 --> 01:08.526
<i>-'Round every bend</i>
-(HONKING)

01:08.985 --> 01:10.695
<i>-Whether racing fast</i>
-(LAUGHS)

01:10.779 --> 01:12.530
<i>-Or getting towed</i>
-(EXCLAIMS)

01:12.614 --> 01:13.615
Whoo-hoo!

01:13.698 --> 01:17.160
<i>Ever together, cars on the road</i>

01:19.412 --> 01:20.955
You grew up here?

01:21.039 --> 01:22.332
Yep. It's funny, though.

01:22.415 --> 01:23.958
When you go back to your old house,

01:24.042 --> 01:26.669
it always looks so much smaller
than you remember it.

01:27.837 --> 01:30.590
Huh. This is not what I expected.

01:30.757 --> 01:32.550
-Hey, do you have an invitation?
-What?

01:32.634 --> 01:35.011
-Mr. McQueen!
-Cruz!

01:35.178 --> 01:38.014
You don't have to call me "Mr. McQueen."

01:38.098 --> 01:39.265
We're both racers now.

01:39.557 --> 01:40.934
Okay, Lightning.

01:42.185 --> 01:44.062
No, I'm sorry. That just sounds weird.

01:44.145 --> 01:47.023
-What are you doing here?
-It's my cousin Mateo's wedding.

01:47.107 --> 01:50.235
He's getting hitched to some
(POSHLY) eccentric socialite.

01:50.318 --> 01:53.988
For your information,
that eccentric satellite is my sister.

01:54.072 --> 01:56.950
Mater! That practically makes us family!

01:57.575 --> 01:59.494
I'm going to be Mater Ramirez!

01:59.828 --> 02:03.164
-I don't think it wo...
-So, how's your off-season treating you?

02:03.248 --> 02:05.291
Great. I started a racing school,

02:05.375 --> 02:08.586
formed a non-profit that provides
snow tires to the lightly treaded,

02:08.670 --> 02:09.754
and I'm learning French.

02:09.879 --> 02:11.923
Wow! That's... (LAUGHS) That's a lot.

02:12.006 --> 02:14.551
<i>Oui.</i> So tell me, what have you been up to?

02:14.884 --> 02:17.971
(SIGHS) I've been on this wild
road trip with Mater,

02:18.054 --> 02:21.349
and to be honest, I am ready to be home.

02:21.432 --> 02:23.643
<i>(HERE COMES THE BRIDE PLAYING)</i>

02:23.726 --> 02:24.853
(CLEARS THROAT)

02:25.311 --> 02:27.188
Oh, boy. There she is.

02:30.108 --> 02:32.026
That's your sister?

02:32.360 --> 02:35.113
I know. It's like seeing double, ain't it?

02:35.697 --> 02:39.492
-Oh, my gosh. (LAUGHS) Baby brother!
-(TIRES SCREECHING)

02:40.201 --> 02:41.244
(BACKFIRES)

02:41.327 --> 02:43.788
Baby brother, baby brother,
baby brother, baby brother!

02:43.872 --> 02:47.959
(GASPS) And who, may I ask,
are these terribly chic guests of yours?

02:48.042 --> 02:50.920
These are my friends. Lightning and Cruz.

02:51.004 --> 02:55.466
And, well, everybody,
this is my dear sister, Mato.

02:55.967 --> 02:56.968
BOTH: Mato?

02:57.051 --> 03:00.096
Yes, like "tomato" without the "to".

03:00.430 --> 03:03.183
-She seems nice.
-Just wait, it's coming.

03:03.308 --> 03:05.310
-Baby brother...
-Wait for it.

03:05.393 --> 03:07.896
...I am so glad you made it.

03:07.979 --> 03:09.272
Wait for it.

03:09.355 --> 03:11.733
Seeing as how no one ever knows

03:11.816 --> 03:13.651
-(GRUNTS) with you.
-And here we go.

03:13.735 --> 03:15.111
With your laid-back, "Aw, shucks.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.322
"Don't need to know
where I'm going to go" attitude,

03:17.405 --> 03:20.325
Nope. I'm not going to bite,
because I'm better than that.

03:20.408 --> 03:24.454
Oh. (SCOFFS) It always comes down
to who's better, doesn't it?

03:24.537 --> 03:26.456
(STAMMERS) That's not what I said!

03:26.539 --> 03:27.874
(GRUNTING)

03:29.042 --> 03:30.668
Nope, nope, nope, nope, nope, nope, nope,

03:30.752 --> 03:33.463
-nope, nope, nope.
-I think we all know the answer to that.

03:33.588 --> 03:35.590
-Don't we?
-(GRUNTING)

03:35.673 --> 03:37.634
Not gonna... (GRUNTING) No. No!

03:37.759 --> 03:39.969
Uh, Mater, are... are you okay?

03:40.053 --> 03:42.263
(BLABBERING, YELPS)

03:42.347 --> 03:45.600
I do believe we know who's better.

03:45.683 --> 03:46.768
(GRUNTS, GASPS)

03:50.480 --> 03:54.108
All right, that's it.
You want to hash it out? Let's go!

03:54.192 --> 03:56.361
Race to the old oak tree.
Driving backwards.

03:56.444 --> 03:57.987
-Go!
-(TIRES SCREECHING)

03:58.196 --> 04:00.323
-Mater!
-What about the wedding?

04:00.406 --> 04:02.492
So, uh, you with the bride or the groom?

04:02.575 --> 04:03.743
Hey, watch it!

04:04.118 --> 04:05.119
Yeah! Whoo!

04:05.203 --> 04:06.412
Winner, winner, lugnut dinner!

04:06.496 --> 04:09.249
(LAUGHS) Okay, how about we, uh,
go back to the wedding?

04:09.332 --> 04:11.542
Best two out of three.
Lawn drawing contest!

04:11.626 --> 04:12.794
Challenge accepted.

04:12.877 --> 04:14.963
Whee-hee! Get 'er done!

04:15.255 --> 04:17.590
MATO: Whoo-hoo! Wee! Yee-haw!

04:18.007 --> 04:19.550
Winner, Mato!

04:19.634 --> 04:21.135
Cruz, what are you doing?

04:21.219 --> 04:23.888
Oh, I also became a certified referee
over the off-season.

04:24.347 --> 04:25.431
Huh.

04:25.515 --> 04:27.350
-Best three out of five!
-Fine!

04:27.433 --> 04:29.769
The first one up the tree wins.
One, two, three, go!

04:29.852 --> 04:31.062
(CREAKING)

04:31.145 --> 04:32.146
All right, buddy.

04:32.230 --> 04:35.233
Hey, why don't we just call this thing
a tie and then we move on, all right?

04:35.316 --> 04:36.734
-A tie?
-BOTH: Never!

04:36.818 --> 04:38.236
-(SHOUTS)
-(CRASHES)

04:38.319 --> 04:40.571
(ENGINE REVVING)

04:40.655 --> 04:42.073
(OPERATIC SINGING)

04:42.156 --> 04:43.157
Ha!

04:43.825 --> 04:44.993
Winner, Mato!

04:45.201 --> 04:47.745
(SLURPING) Done. Done. Done.

04:47.870 --> 04:48.955
Winner, Mater!

04:49.038 --> 04:50.373
BOTH: One, two, three, rock!

04:50.456 --> 04:51.749
One, two, three, rock!

04:51.833 --> 04:53.209
One, two, three, rock!

04:53.543 --> 04:56.713
C-H-I-A-R-O-S-C-U-R-I-S-T. Chiaroscurist.

04:57.046 --> 04:58.506
Correct. Mater!

04:59.340 --> 05:00.341
Ow!

05:00.425 --> 05:01.718
-Slug bug!
-Mato!

05:02.719 --> 05:04.012
-Ow!
-Nebraska!

05:04.220 --> 05:05.221
Mater!

05:05.638 --> 05:06.681
Mato!

05:07.932 --> 05:08.975
Mater! Mato!

05:09.183 --> 05:10.310
Mater! Mato!

05:10.393 --> 05:11.561
Mater!

05:11.644 --> 05:13.021
-Stare off!
-Go!

05:17.233 --> 05:19.610
-(BUZZING)
-(YELPING) Bug in my eye! Get it out!

05:19.694 --> 05:21.904
Winner, Mato!

05:21.988 --> 05:24.907
(LAUGHS) Whoo! That's it! 51 out of 100!

05:24.991 --> 05:27.118
I win! I win! Y'all!

05:27.201 --> 05:28.786
(MATO LAUGHING)

05:28.870 --> 05:31.414
All right, already.
You ain't gotta toot your own horn

05:31.497 --> 05:34.083
-and be so dramatic about it.
-I'm not dramatic. I'm passionate.

05:34.167 --> 05:36.627
Not like you, just rolling through life
without a care in the world.

05:36.711 --> 05:39.630
Me? At least I don't have to broadcast
every last thing that crosses my mind.

05:39.714 --> 05:40.757
-(BOTH MOCKING)
-Wait!

05:41.132 --> 05:42.216
Uh...

05:42.300 --> 05:45.219
Did I mention I dabble in family therapy?

05:48.139 --> 05:51.809
Well, I think we had
a very transformative conversation.

05:52.060 --> 05:54.312
Mater, are you back to normal?

05:54.479 --> 05:57.940
Yep. Turns out, we actually
kind of admire each other.

05:58.191 --> 06:00.860
Sometimes, I wish I could share
anything I'm feeling.

06:00.943 --> 06:02.737
(LAUGHS) Just like my big sis.

06:02.820 --> 06:06.032
And I wish that I could just let things
slide once in a while,

06:06.115 --> 06:07.283
like my baby brother.

06:07.367 --> 06:09.827
No, no, no. But you can't.
Just a moment more, please.

06:09.911 --> 06:12.205
I've waited long enough.
I don't have time for this.

06:12.288 --> 06:14.457
I've got other things to do with my day.

06:16.209 --> 06:18.294
(SIGHS) I'm sorry, <i>mi amore.</i>

06:18.586 --> 06:19.962
I guess the wedding's off.

06:20.838 --> 06:22.006
Not to worry.

06:22.340 --> 06:24.217
I'm also a licensed wedding officiant.

06:24.300 --> 06:26.052
(LAUGHS) Of course you are.

06:27.011 --> 06:30.807
-I now pronounce you married!
-(ALL CHEERING)

06:30.890 --> 06:33.893
<i>(WEDDING MARCH PLAYING)</i>

06:34.018 --> 06:37.146
-(SOFT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)
-(LIVELY CHATTER)

06:37.230 --> 06:39.774
Wow. That was a strange day.

06:39.857 --> 06:42.735
Yeah, well, par for the course
for this road trip.

06:43.111 --> 06:45.488
So you didn't have a good time with Mater?

06:45.905 --> 06:47.782
No, no, no. Mater is great.

06:47.949 --> 06:51.702
But (SIGHS) let's just say
it'll be a relief to fly back home

06:51.786 --> 06:53.871
to my own calm, normal life.

06:55.706 --> 06:57.250
-Wha... Why?
-(GLASS CLINKING)

06:57.333 --> 06:58.584
(PEOPLE SHUSHING)

06:58.668 --> 07:01.504
Attention, friends and folks,
friends and folks.

07:01.587 --> 07:03.840
While it's true my dear old sis and I

07:03.923 --> 07:06.551
ain't spent much time together
over the years.

07:06.634 --> 07:08.636
Well, that's...
that's all going to change.

07:09.303 --> 07:13.099
Because, you see, uh...
Well, I guess what I'm trying to say is

07:13.808 --> 07:18.062
we may only have a short amount
of time left on this planet.

07:18.563 --> 07:22.275
So we've got to make the most of that time
with the ones we care for.

07:22.817 --> 07:26.112
What course we decide upon
might prove scary at times.

07:26.195 --> 07:27.738
<i>Or test our resolve.</i>

07:27.989 --> 07:29.657
<i>Or maybe even make us question</i>

07:29.740 --> 07:33.995
<i>the very reasons for embarking</i>
<i>on this grand journey in the first place.</i>

07:34.203 --> 07:39.041
But it is true, them unexpected turns,
all the bumps along the road,

07:39.167 --> 07:41.335
that's what makes life worth living.

07:43.212 --> 07:44.255
(CLEARS THROAT)

07:44.338 --> 07:46.174
Uh... Uh...

07:46.466 --> 07:48.759
And that is why, as your president,

07:48.843 --> 07:50.970
I call upon the cars of the world

07:51.137 --> 07:54.015
to rise up against
this zombie alien invasion

07:54.140 --> 07:56.684
and to squelch the brainy-headed scourge,

07:56.767 --> 08:00.313
or else it's only a matter of time
before they blow up the Earth.

08:00.897 --> 08:01.898
Thank you.

08:02.356 --> 08:03.733
-BOTH: What the...
-Huh?

08:03.816 --> 08:06.110
(LAUGHS) To the bride and groom!

08:06.194 --> 08:07.195
(ALL CHEERING)

08:07.278 --> 08:09.447
Hey, honey bun,
wanna race to the wedding cake?

08:09.655 --> 08:11.908
<i>Mi amore,</i>
I wouldn't have it any other way.

08:12.283 --> 08:13.493
One, two, three, go!

08:13.701 --> 08:15.620
(CANS CLATTERING)

08:18.831 --> 08:19.999
Nice speech, buddy.

08:20.208 --> 08:23.085
You know, I can't help but think
I've heard it somewhere before.

08:23.169 --> 08:24.879
Well, I couldn't let it go to waste.

08:25.296 --> 08:28.382
It was really great seeing you guys.
Have a safe flight back.

08:28.883 --> 08:30.927
Oh. (CHUCKLES) Yeah.

08:31.886 --> 08:34.096
Actually, I was thinking we should drive.

08:34.180 --> 08:37.099
-(GASPS) Really?
-You know, take our time.

08:37.183 --> 08:40.102
Wander the back roads,
maybe even make new friends.

08:40.186 --> 08:42.313
Hey, where do you think
we ought to stop tonight?

08:42.438 --> 08:43.439
Don't know.

08:43.523 --> 08:46.943
Let's just see what the old road
has in store for us, bumps and all.

08:47.026 --> 08:48.945
You know, I think we should see
the wax museums

08:49.028 --> 08:50.196
we skipped over on the way out.

08:50.279 --> 08:51.489
That's on my bucket list.

08:51.572 --> 08:53.824
-Hey, you ever driven through...
-See you on the track, racer.

08:53.908 --> 08:56.202
Oh, you got it, Lightning.

08:56.285 --> 08:57.828
Ooh! Nope. No.

08:58.037 --> 08:59.288
-Still sounds weird.
-(LAUGHS)

08:59.372 --> 09:01.666
I'll tell you what,
you pick the first three stops.

09:01.791 --> 09:02.875
I get the next 12.

09:02.959 --> 09:04.877
(LAUGHS) Yeah.

09:06.045 --> 09:09.507
<i>Hittin' the highway, a couple of friends</i>

09:09.590 --> 09:13.719
<i>With new adventures 'round every bend</i>

09:13.803 --> 09:17.848
<i>Whether racing fast or getting towed</i>

09:18.015 --> 09:22.144
<i>They're ever together, cars on the road</i>

09:22.228 --> 09:26.357
<i>Winding along the blue lines</i>
<i>So much to see</i>

09:26.440 --> 09:30.444
<i>Harrowing... and thrilling mysteries</i>

09:30.528 --> 09:34.574
<i>Crazy situations</i>
<i>They still can't quite believe</i>

09:34.657 --> 09:39.328
<i>So much unexpected</i>
<i>But everything they need</i>

09:39.412 --> 09:42.957
<i>'Cause when you are on the road</i>
<i>And traveling friends</i>

09:43.165 --> 09:47.420
<i>You might not know where you're going</i>
<i>But you sure know where you've been</i>

09:47.545 --> 09:51.507
<i>And when the trip is over</i>
<i>And the stories told</i>

09:51.632 --> 09:55.928
<i>You'll always hold on</i>
<i>To that feeling of being</i>

09:56.095 --> 09:59.599
<i>When you are on the road</i>
<i>And traveling with friends</i>

09:59.765 --> 10:04.395
<i>Might not know where you're going</i>
<i>But you sure know where you've been</i>

10:04.520 --> 10:08.482
<i>And when the trip is over</i>
<i>And the stories told</i>

10:08.566 --> 10:13.279
<i>You'll always hold on</i>
<i>To that feeling of being</i>

10:13.446 --> 10:16.449
<i>Cars on the road</i>

10:21.329 --> 10:24.165
Hey, I wonder where they went
on their honeymoon.

10:24.540 --> 10:25.958
-Mateo!
-Mato!

10:26.042 --> 10:27.168
-Mateo!
-Mato!

10:27.251 --> 10:28.502
Mateo!

10:33.090 --> 10:34.133
(CLICKS)
